# =============================================================================
# Oracle kernel .gitignore
#
# Policy (design principle: "Ledgers are tracked AND classified"):
#   * Confidential/local stores live under *.nosync/ and are NOT committed.
#   * EXCEPT the two append-only stores that ARE institutional memory and must
#     be backed up + recoverable from git: the Meta ledgers and the Workproduct
#     registries. These are negate-tracked back in below.
#   * Those tracked ledgers/registries carry METADATA ONLY (drop_id, ts, actor,
#     classification, destination, ...), never secret payloads — see SECURITY.md
#     ("ledger-tracking sensitivity statement") and the export_event schema
#     (no payload/content field). A lint check enforces this.
#   * Real secrets live ONLY in .env.nosync (git-ignored) and are read via
#     load-env.sh; .env.example carries variable NAMES only.
#
# git semantics note: to un-ignore a path inside an ignored directory you must
# first re-include each parent directory, then the file glob. That is why each
# negate block re-includes the directory chain before the *.jsonl / REGISTRY.md.
# =============================================================================

# --- Local / confidential stores (ignored by default) -----------------------
*.nosync/
*.nosync

# --- Tracked: Meta append-only ledgers (metadata only) -----------------------
# export_event.jsonl, redaction_event.jsonl, action_event.jsonl, loop_runs.jsonl
!Meta.nosync/
Meta.nosync/*
!Meta.nosync/ledgers/
!Meta.nosync/ledgers/*.jsonl

# --- Tracked: Workproduct artifact registries --------------------------------
# Human-readable REGISTRY.md plus the machine .registry.jsonl drop ledgers.
!Workproduct.nosync/
Workproduct.nosync/*
!Workproduct.nosync/_INPUT/
!Workproduct.nosync/_OUTPUT/
!Workproduct.nosync/_INPUT/REGISTRY.md
!Workproduct.nosync/_OUTPUT/REGISTRY.md
!Workproduct.nosync/_INPUT/.registry.jsonl
!Workproduct.nosync/_OUTPUT/.registry.jsonl

# --- Secrets: NEVER committed ------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Setup scratch -----------------------------------------------------------
.setup-session/
tmp.nosync/

# --- Derived / rebuildable ---------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/

# --- Local OS / editor noise -------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
